    &lt;Title&gt;It’s a conveyer belt. They keep guessing until it works.&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Thegreek1979&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Been unlucky enough to visit the rheumatologist department 3 times so far. The nurses that do the pre checks are lovely and caring but the Rheumatologist is brutal and rude. Did not want to listen to me or consider my concerns. Was put on Methotrexate despite voicing concerns. After three months when they didn’t work I was put on to a different drug. The explanation was “ we now know that didn’t work so we’ll use it as a diagnostic tool” was eventually referred for MRI and the results came back “ there were technical issues and not all images were available “ I was told that it didn’t matter as the rheumatologist had the clinical facts to confirm the diagnosis. Been on the new drugs for 13 weeks and still in pain with no improvements. Went for my third visit and saw the nurse who couldn’t answer any of my questions or concerns. Spoke to my GP and he’s happy to refer me somewhere else for a second opinion. So far every doctor or professional I’ve spoken to disagrees with the rheumatologists diagnosis but won’t commit due to not being a rheumatologist. This is has been going on for 18 months and the drugs I’m on are damaging my kidneys and suppressing my immune system without any improvement. Despite my blood results showing normal inflammation from the start.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
